				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">BTW, though I should mention an SMS game which used a creative solution for the status bar vs. vertical scroll issue: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-I1ZHMMwLwA" class="postlink">Ys</a><br /><br />The words are sprites, but the meters are background tiles. Since they don't have any vertical details, they can be drawn taller than they need to be and only a section of each is displayed with raster effects. They always start and end at the same screen positions, but the actual tiles are scrolling vertically, which can't be noticed because there are no vertical details.<br /><br />The same concept could probably be used for more complex status bars, if you used symbols instead of words to indicate what's being measured, and bars, squares, sticks, or anything else without vertical details to measure/count stuff.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

