			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, later NTSC systems also had the fixed VDP, it's just that in those territories it was kind of useless since you couldn't rely on everybody having it. But on other places it was a safe bet, to the point that Codemasters would always use the 224 height resolution instead of the 192 one (I wonder if they were even aware that the 224 one wasn't present in all consoles).<br /><br />But yeah, it's likely that TecToy's systems were using the fixed VDP. I'm not sure if they were using PAL-M though (Brazil is next to a PAL-N territory after all, many TVs were NTSC + PAL-N + PAL-M compatible, and they also sold consoles in Argentina which is a PAL-N territory).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

